<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-094-074 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 278 617</DOCID><JOURNAL>The LocalNetter  August 1991 v11 n8 p39(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New release of Recital hits the street. (Recital 7.0 databasemanagement system) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Recital Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Recital 7.0 (Data base management system) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData Base Management Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW RELEASE OF RECITAL HITS THE STREETSandM;Recital Corporation has released Recital 7.0, offering enhanced databasemanagement capabilities for developers and added productivity features.andP;  Thecompany has added such features as a built-in &quot;dynamic compiler,&quot; a pop-uptime management scheduler, relational multi-record table fields in forms,split-screen relational browse, and database, form, and report triggers.andM;Recital is a fourth-generation application development environment (4GE) witha built-in relational database management system for UNIX and VAX/VMSplatforms.andP;  Its Client/Server architecture is designed to facilitateinformation management across both homogeneous and heterogeneous networkedcomputing environments.andM;At the center of the Recital engine is the Applications Data Dictionary.andO;This dictionary takes an object-oriented view of application developmentwhere components of applications are predefined, stored, and used asapplications objects.andP;  Support for triggers, business rules, procedures,referential integrity, and validations may be defined at the database, form,and report levels.andP;  Xbase applications written in dBASE III+, dBASE IV,Foxbase, and Clipper can be migrated to more than 100 UNIX and VAX/VMScomputers without program modification.andM;The company is offering a free Technical Overview of Recital that providesdetails on the product and its application.andP;  Free 30-day evaluations are alsoavailable.andM;Information:  Barry Marvin, Recital Corporation, 85 Constitution Lane,Danvers, MA 01923; (508) 750-1066, Fax (508) 750-8097.andO;</TEXT></DOC>